  "texts": [
    "This sampler is designed to assign a confidence score to each candidate region and filter out irrelevant or uninformative areas (e.g., regions without ANA cells).",
    "This step ensures that only high-quality instances are used for downstream prediction.The learning process can thus be formulated as a two-stage inference:ŷj i = F S(x j i, α j i,k, t j i,k),(2)ŷi = G {ŷ j i } Ni j=1.",
    "(3)where S(•) is the instance sampler function, F(•) is the instance-level prediction function, and G(•) denotes the aggregation function that synthesizes instance-level outputs into an image-level prediction ŷi.",
    "The learning objective minimizes the instance-level binary cross-entropy between ŷj i and the pseudo-label ξj i produced by D (Sec. III-D).",
    "However, only image-level ground-truth labels y i are available in real-world scenarios, and instance-level annotations y j i are typically not provided."
  ],
